### 7. Error Handling Patterns

**Try-Catch at Command Level:**
```typescript
try {
  // Main work
} catch (error) {
  if (this.isShuttingDown) {
    this.logger.warn('Command interrupted during shutdown');
    return;
  }
  this.logger.error(`Failed: ${(error as Error).message}`);
  process.exit(1);
}
```

**Individual Batch Error Handling:**
```typescript
const result = await Promise.allSettled(promises);
result.forEach((r, index) => {
  if (r.status === 'rejected') {
    this.logger.error(`Batch ${index} failed: ${r.reason}`);
    rollbar.error(new Error(`Batch failed`), { batchIndex: index });
  }
});
```

**Service-Level Cancellation:**
- Services maintain `isCancelled` flag
- Check flag at processing boundaries
- Allow graceful interruption mid-operation

