### Summary Table: Pattern Selection

| Scenario | Pattern | Why |
|----------|---------|-----|
| CPU-intensive transforms | Worker Threads | Parallel compute without event loop blocking |
| API calls (Algolia writes) | Concurrency Queue | Respect rate limits, manage connections |
| Mixed transform + API | Both combined | Workers transform â†’ Queue makes API calls |
| Simple sequential work | Sequential chunks | Simpler, easier to debug |
| Historical time-based data | Year/Month chunking | Natural boundaries, idempotency |
| Needs graceful cancel | All patterns + flag | Always add cancellation support |

This analysis provides a complete blueprint for implementing an efficient weekly re-indexing job that scales to 30k+ products while maintaining reliability, monitorability, and graceful degradation.
